WEBVTT

00:00:01.188 --> 00:00:09.947 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Take a moment now and picture the scene.
Up ahead on the path are what seem to be

00:00:09.947 --> 00:00:19.373 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Children laughing at play
In a world free of the fears we once faced.

00:00:19.373 --> 00:00:28.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And taking care of this beautiful earth
Are a people that live by our Father’s words:

00:00:28.382 --> 00:00:38.601 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Until the moon is no more”—
There is the peace we have been waiting for.

00:00:38.601 --> 00:00:47.443 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We will feel His love
Under the rule of His Son

00:00:47.443 --> 00:00:53.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the new world to come.

00:00:58.454 --> 00:01:03.000 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hope is a fire in our hearts.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.046 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hope is an anchor that holds us firm.

00:01:07.046 --> 00:01:11.175 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hope is a light that shines like the sun

00:01:11.175 --> 00:01:15.930 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As we see ourselves there

00:01:15.930 --> 00:01:21.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the new world to come.

00:01:26.440 --> 00:01:30.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Take a moment now and think of a place

00:01:30.444 --> 00:01:35.658 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
By the mountains and rivers or wide open plains.

00:01:35.658 --> 00:01:39.870 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s a place to call home.

00:01:39.870 --> 00:01:45.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And now walking in through your front door,

00:01:45.209 --> 00:01:49.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There is someone that you know

00:01:49.797 --> 00:01:54.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Holding out his open arms in hopes

00:01:54.259 --> 00:01:57.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Of a tearful embrace—

00:01:57.680 --> 00:02:02.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Feels like forever since you’ve been face-to-face.

